`,oP=el.A.div`
  button span {
    //  n.b. The reason for this font size transformation and then scale down is due to how chromium renders for retina
    //  displays. It always has some weird spacing on the right side. To solve, we double then halve which for some reason
    //  fixes it. https://stackoverflow.com/a/59688437
    //  We do still want it bigger than "normal", so instead of a scale up we just scale slightly larger than half.
    //  The related chrome bug https://issues.chromium.org/issues/41214988 is fixed for _some_ mac displays -
    //  on my machine it is broken on an external monitor attached to the display, but it's fixed if you drag the window
    //  onto the laptop. pls apple & chromium fix; but for now this is a workaround to make it look _slightly_ less worse.
    font-size: calc(var(--lns-fontSize-medium) * 2);
    transform: ${e=>e.isMobile?"scale(1)":"scale(0.7)"};
  }
`,oL=el.A.li`
  transition: transform 0.1s;
